[ Applause ]

00:08:27.130 --> 00:08:31.840
&gt;&gt; Thank you for the introduction.

00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:34.210
I'm so happy to be in
this beautiful place,

00:08:34.210 --> 00:08:38.410
talking about my passion,
Islamic architecture.

00:08:38.410 --> 00:08:44.050
Have you ever thought why it
is called Islamic architecture?

00:08:44.050 --> 00:08:46.490
Like we are talking
about civilizations

00:08:46.490 --> 00:08:51.910
that have covered massive
areas from west to east,

00:08:51.910 --> 00:08:54.550
yet it is named with a belief.

00:08:54.550 --> 00:08:58.530
If we want to talk about
civilizations that were based

00:08:58.530 --> 00:09:03.050 position:56%
on religion, like Christian
architecture or Jewish architecture,

00:09:03.050 --> 00:09:06.350
they are never labeled
with their beliefs,

00:09:06.350 --> 00:09:09.270
except Islamic architecture.

00:09:09.270 --> 00:09:11.190
Have you thought of it?

00:09:11.190 --> 00:09:15.610
In reality, Islamic
architecture is not about a space

00:09:15.610 --> 00:09:19.300
to play, it's not about a mosque.

00:09:19.300 --> 00:09:22.010
It is philosophies in art.

00:09:22.010 --> 00:09:27.150
Philosophies, and selection and
creating elements, patterns.

00:09:27.150 --> 00:09:31.410
So today, I'm going to talk
about these philosophies

00:09:31.410 --> 00:09:38.110
that I have figured out while in
my research, doing my PhD study.

00:09:38.110 --> 00:09:44.140 position:56%
Let's go back to the birth of Islam.

00:09:44.140 --> 00:09:46.970
It started in Medina.

00:09:46.970 --> 00:09:51.190
There was no architecture at
that time, only mud buildings,

00:09:51.190 --> 00:09:53.600
like traditional buildings.

00:09:53.600 --> 00:09:56.770
Only one structure was
in the Arabian Peninsula,

00:09:56.770 --> 00:09:58.400
which was [foreign term].

00:09:58.400 --> 00:10:03.970
A prophet of Islam was
died, and they have moved

00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:10.030
and shifted the capital of Islam
to the north, to the [inaudible].

00:10:10.030 --> 00:10:16.360
And the first Islamic civilization
was called [foreign word spoken].

00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:17.660
In Arabic, [Arabic word spoken].

00:10:17.660 --> 00:10:25.370
So what has happened, from being in
a desert, in an Arabian peninsula,

00:10:25.370 --> 00:10:30.810
they have shifted, and was
exposed to the Roman architecture,

00:10:30.810 --> 00:10:35.560
Byzantine architecture,
and Sassanid architecture.

00:10:35.560 --> 00:10:40.940
It was like a shock seeing
[inaudible], mosaic, domes,

00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:44.250
seeing this massive
architecture of Roman.

00:10:44.250 --> 00:10:47.660
So they got influenced
with these elements.

00:10:47.660 --> 00:10:52.490
Now, when we go back
to Islam...oops,

00:10:52.490 --> 00:10:56.360
the [foreign word spoken]
was a temple.

00:10:56.360 --> 00:11:01.180
It was not a mosque.

00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:06.770
The methodologies at that time was
converting a temple to a mosque,

00:11:06.770 --> 00:11:09.370
converting a church to a mosque.

00:11:09.370 --> 00:11:12.370
So this was the methodology.

00:11:12.370 --> 00:11:19.490
Why? Economically,
easy, shows power.

00:11:19.490 --> 00:11:25.990
So what has happened, after
Islam, this temple was converted,

00:11:25.990 --> 00:11:29.230
and became a mosque, and
it's called The Holy Mosque,

00:11:29.230 --> 00:11:32.760
and located in Mecca.

00:11:32.760 --> 00:11:37.310
Now, [inaudible], the faith
of Islam has expanded.

00:11:37.310 --> 00:11:43.710
The east, to Persia, Central Asia,

00:11:43.710 --> 00:11:47.520
and west to North Africa,
and south Europe.

00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:53.950
So these massive lands were
covered with-were consisting

00:11:53.950 --> 00:11:55.910
of Islamic architecture.

00:11:55.910 --> 00:12:03.700
When we talk about Islamic
architecture, it is classified.

00:12:03.700 --> 00:12:07.730
Each period of time,
there was Islamic dynasty,

00:12:07.730 --> 00:12:12.360
and each dynasty has
its own architecture.

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:17.470
By reviewing these elements, you
would know the name of the dynasty.

00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:23.200
So let me just go through
these dynasties.

00:12:23.200 --> 00:12:26.720
The first dynasty was the Umayyad.

00:12:26.720 --> 00:12:32.590
And then, Abbasid architecture,

00:12:32.590 --> 00:12:36.380
which is in Arabic,
[Arabic term spoken].

00:12:36.380 --> 00:12:40.560
Tulunid architecture, which
is [foreign word spoken].

00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:44.220
Fatimid architecture, which
is [foreign word spoken].

00:12:44.220 --> 00:12:47.510
Aghlabid architecture, which
is [foreign word spoken],

00:12:47.510 --> 00:12:50.150
Seljuk architecture, which
is [foreign word spoken].

00:12:50.150 --> 00:12:53.720
Ottoman architecture, which
is [foreign word spoken].

00:12:53.720 --> 00:12:57.010
And Mughal architecture, which
is [foreign word spoken].

00:12:57.010 --> 00:13:02.910
So these are part of the
Islamic architecture element.

00:13:02.910 --> 00:13:09.500
Whenever you see them,
you understand

00:13:09.500 --> 00:13:12.500
that these empires
were in these lands.

00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:16.030
How this architecture has
transferred-you're talking

00:13:16.030 --> 00:13:17.330
about massive area.

00:13:17.330 --> 00:13:21.230
Miles, it's west and east.

00:13:21.230 --> 00:13:33.000
Like, if you take a plane to
these places, it takes hours.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:36.870
What about traveling using camels?

00:13:36.870 --> 00:13:41.890
So these road trips
used to called caravans.

00:13:41.890 --> 00:13:44.450
A caravan site.

00:13:44.450 --> 00:13:50.810
In ancient times, there
were two routes,

00:13:50.810 --> 00:13:53.670
one in the summer,
and one in the winter.

00:13:53.670 --> 00:14:00.120
It started from China, going to
Afghanistan, from Afghanistan

00:14:00.120 --> 00:14:07.180 position:56%
to Khorasan, a road from Afghanistan
to Persia, and from Persia going

00:14:07.180 --> 00:14:11.180
to Iraq, and from Iraq,
you go back to Damascus,

00:14:11.180 --> 00:14:13.290
and from Damascus,
you have two roads.

00:14:13.290 --> 00:14:18.470
You go to Europe, to Italy, or
you take another road from Iraq

00:14:18.470 --> 00:14:23.480
to Egypt, from Egypt to Morocco,
and from Morocco to Spain.

00:14:23.480 --> 00:14:26.060
So these were the stations.

00:14:26.060 --> 00:14:34.440 position:56%
The caravan used to have like people
used to carry animals, carry food,

00:14:34.440 --> 00:14:38.650
carry art, carry human being.

00:14:38.650 --> 00:14:44.850
So it's a long road trip, and
culture used to go back and forth.

00:14:47.910 --> 00:14:54.350
The thing is, when you look and
observe the Islamic architecture,

00:14:54.350 --> 00:14:59.250
just like amazing art
with philosophies

00:14:59.250 --> 00:15:02.940
that sometimes-like
it has definition.

00:15:02.940 --> 00:15:07.690
It can be like all of a sudden
this architecture was created.

00:15:07.690 --> 00:15:09.430
So I had this curiosity

00:15:09.430 --> 00:15:14.060
of understanding how these
patterns were created.

00:15:14.060 --> 00:15:15.360
The bricks.

00:15:15.360 --> 00:15:19.970
How they are overlapping, the
orientation, the calligraphy.

00:15:19.970 --> 00:15:21.890
From where was the start?

00:15:21.890 --> 00:15:25.640 position:56%
You're talking about decades of art.

00:15:25.640 --> 00:15:30.240
So, my passion toward
this started in Spain.

00:15:30.240 --> 00:15:31.540
Did anyone go to [inaudible]?

00:15:31.540 --> 00:15:34.460
Oh, lucky you!

00:15:34.460 --> 00:15:35.760
One, two, three, four!

00:15:35.760 --> 00:15:37.990
Oh! I have friends here.

00:15:37.990 --> 00:15:39.550
Did you get this feeling

00:15:39.550 --> 00:15:46.070
of like tremendous art,
that have significance?

00:15:46.070 --> 00:15:50.580
That you cannot understand
from how much the beauty of it?

00:15:50.580 --> 00:15:53.850
So I started, because
it's part of my culture,

00:15:53.850 --> 00:15:58.060
wanting to understand these
philosophies, and linking religion

00:15:58.060 --> 00:16:01.020
to these philosophies,
how they were developed.

00:16:01.020 --> 00:16:11.780
So in Granada, which is Alhambra,
I was like every time you go there,

00:16:11.780 --> 00:16:15.480
you feel like you never saw
it, because it is lots of art

00:16:15.480 --> 00:16:20.770
that you cannot observe from
one time, from one visit.

00:16:20.770 --> 00:16:27.480
Observing these architectural
elements, the bricks, the stones,

00:16:27.480 --> 00:16:34.490
the arches, the colors,
the domes, the details,

00:16:34.490 --> 00:16:37.470
and here was the big shock.

00:16:37.470 --> 00:16:38.950
What is this?

00:16:38.950 --> 00:16:42.690
How can you identify this element?

00:16:42.690 --> 00:16:44.340
Is it a dome?

00:16:44.340 --> 00:16:48.030
Like, what can we call this?

00:16:48.030 --> 00:16:51.170
It's tremendous art
that you cannot explain,

00:16:51.170 --> 00:16:54.470
and I wanted to know how
they have created it.

00:16:54.470 --> 00:16:57.270
How is the structure,
the construction,

00:16:57.270 --> 00:16:59.470
how many years it took them.

00:16:59.470 --> 00:17:04.130
So I started searching for
philosophies, and understanding,

00:17:04.130 --> 00:17:10.540
going to vintage shops, trying
to buy books, to understand it.

00:17:10.540 --> 00:17:15.850
And I'm having here, like it is
tall, connected with the wall,

00:17:15.850 --> 00:17:19.770
with the ceiling, but you
cannot describe the space.

00:17:20.790 --> 00:17:27.040
So I started-I figured out one
of the great philosophies in art,

00:17:27.040 --> 00:17:31.360
in Islamic art, which is
called the panic of emptiness.

00:17:31.360 --> 00:17:37.780
And it to me is that a flat form,

00:17:37.780 --> 00:17:40.350
and you extrude it,
so it's like panic.

00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:47.450
And from here, the concept of these
elements started to be created,

00:17:47.450 --> 00:17:51.730
like they designed these
patterns, flat designs,

00:17:51.730 --> 00:17:55.040
and then they extrude
it and make it 3D.

00:17:55.040 --> 00:17:57.630
So I wanted to know more
about these patterns

00:17:57.630 --> 00:18:00.140
from where they were abstracted.

00:18:00.140 --> 00:18:07.780
And I found vintage
drawings from Persia.

00:18:07.780 --> 00:18:14.360
And I started to think and analyze,
and read more, and surprisingly,

00:18:14.360 --> 00:18:19.650
these patterns were
extracted from Quran.

00:18:19.650 --> 00:18:23.620
These, the Quran is
the book, for Muslims.

00:18:23.620 --> 00:18:30.290
And they started translating these
